<% content_for :title, "Waitlist — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Waitlist", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Waitlist</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">Get notified by email when studio time becomes available.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">What Is the Waitlist?</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            The waitlist lets you receive an email notification when new studio slots open up —
            so you don't have to keep checking back manually. When slots become available, everyone
            on the waitlist gets a single email with a link to the booking calendar.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">How to Join</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            When the studio calendar has no available slots, a <strong>Join waitlist</strong> button
            appears on the home page below the "No upcoming slots" message. Click it and you're on
            the list — you'll receive a notification email the next time slots are added or a booking
            is cancelled.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must be signed in to join. If you don't have an account yet,
            <%= link_to "create one here", new_registration_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">When Will I Get an Email?</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>A notification is sent when any of the following happens:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
            <li>The studio adds new slots to the calendar</li>
            <li>Another customer cancels a booking, releasing those hours</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The email goes to the address on your account and includes a direct link to the home page
            so you can book right away.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">How to Leave</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            If you no longer want notifications, visit the home page while no slots are available.
            You'll see a <strong>Leave waitlist</strong> button. Click it and you'll be removed
            immediately.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Rejoining After Being Notified</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            After you receive a notification email, your spot in the waitlist is marked as notified.
            If you check the calendar and the slots are already gone, or if no slots fit your schedule,
            simply click <strong>Join waitlist</strong> again from the home page to re-activate your
            entry. You'll be notified again the next time slots become available.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
